15 WHEREAS, Muslims celebrate two Eid "festivals" every lunar
16 year, Eid Al-Fitr and Eid Al-Adha; and
17 WHEREAS, Eid Al-Fitr, or "festival of breaking of the fast,"
18 is celebrated first at the conclusion of the Muslim holy month
19 of Ramadan; and
20 WHEREAS, Muslims in the United States observe this time of
21 sacrifice and contemplation by fasting, reading the Holy Qur'an,
22 participating in charity work and worship, and emphasizing self-
23 discipline; and
24
